Intensity family plots

Source: R/plots_boxplot.R, R/plots_violin.R, R/mod_plots_intensity.R
intensity_plots.Rd

These functions are plotting different views of quantitative data. Two plots are available:

  • boxplotD() xxxx,

  • violinPlotD() xxxx.

boxPlotD(object, exp.design, subset = NULL, pal.name = NULL)

violinPlotD(object, exp.design, subset = NULL, pal.name)

mod_intensity_plots_ui(id)

mod_intensity_plots_server(id, object, exp.design, ...)

Arguments

object

xxx

exp.design

xxx

subset

A vector of index indicating rows to highlight

pal.name

xxx

id

xxx

...

xxx

Value

A boxplot A violinplot NA NA

Author

Samuel Wieczorek, Anais Courtier, Enora Fremy

Samuel Wieczorek, Anais Courtier, Enora Fremy

# ----------------------------------------------------
# A shiny module which can track entities on the plots
# ----------------------------------------------------

if (interactive()){
library(QFeatures)
library(shiny)
library(shinyjs)
library(highcharter)
library(DaparToolshed)

data(ft)


ui <- tagList(
  mod_intensity_plots_ui('iplots'),
  uiOutput('show')
)

server <- function(input, output, session) {
  rv <- reactiveValues(
    tmp = NULL
  )
  
  mod_intensity_plots_server(id = 'iplots',
                             object = reactive({ft[[1]]}),
                             exp.design = reactive({design(ft)}),
                             pal.name = 'Dark2'
                             )
  
}
shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)
}
